30
00:03:41,237 --> 00:03:42,534
This must be faced,,,

31
00:03:42,738 --> 00:03:46,196
,,,as there are many
ramifications and complications,

32
00:03:46,408 --> 00:03:49,400
Many promises were made, et cetera,

33
00:03:49,845 --> 00:03:53,337
I need an open exchange
with you to clear things,

34
00:03:53,549 --> 00:03:55,414
For all of us to go on,,,

35
00:03:55,618 --> 00:03:59,918
,,, the situation has got to be
confronted in some fashion,

36
00:04:00,122 --> 00:04:03,023
Please contact me at this number,

37
00:04:03,225 --> 00:04:05,785
I want what`s best for everyone,

38
00:04:05,995 --> 00:04:07,690
Dolores Paley,

39
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:35,787
That the new ophthalmology wing
has become a reality...

40
00:04:35,991 --> 00:04:39,859
...is not just a tribute to me
but to a spirit of community...

41
00:04:40,062 --> 00:04:43,998
...generosity, of mutual caring
and answered prayers.

42
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:48,032
lt`s funny l use the term
``answered prayers.``

43
00:04:48,237 --> 00:04:49,795
l`m a man of science.

44
00:04:50,005 --> 00:04:53,964
l`ve always been a skeptic,
but l was raised religiously.

45
00:04:54,176 --> 00:04:56,474
l challenged it, even as a child...

46
00:04:57,179 --> 00:05:00,205
,,,but some of that feeling
stuck with me,

47
00:05:00,849 --> 00:05:03,215
I remember my father telling me,`

48
00:05:03,419 --> 00:05:06,286
``The eyes of God are on us always, ``

49
00:05:06,789 --> 00:05:08,484
``The eyes of God.``

50
00:05:09,391 --> 00:05:12,121
What a phrase to a young boy.

51
00:05:12,328 --> 00:05:14,956
l mean, what were God`s eyes like?

52
00:05:15,297 --> 00:05:19,734
Unimaginably penetrating,
intense eyes, l assumed.

53
00:05:20,603 --> 00:05:25,939
l wonder if it was just a coincidence
that l specialized in ophthalmology.

54
00:05:28,544 --> 00:05:32,810
l`m so proud of you, Judah.
Sharon is, we all are.

55
00:05:33,582 --> 00:05:35,174
All together.

56
00:05:59,608 --> 00:06:03,203
-Why did you write the letter?
-We`ve been through it.

57
00:06:03,412 --> 00:06:05,539
You wanna destroy my family?

58
00:06:05,748 --> 00:06:08,114
l want her to know her husband.

59
00:06:08,317 --> 00:06:12,913
lt was lying there all day.
By sheer chance, she didn`t open it.

60
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:16,148
You said you`d leave Miriam!
We made plans!

61
00:06:16,358 --> 00:06:17,484
-l didn`t.
-You did!

62
00:06:17,693 --> 00:06:19,422
l gave up opportunities!

63
00:06:19,628 --> 00:06:21,926
-Pipe dreams.
-Other men wanted me.

64
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:24,964
What do you want?
You think this is easy?

65
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:28,659
l want what you told me
you wanted, to be together.

66
00:06:28,871 --> 00:06:32,671
Otherwise, l don`t know what!
l`ll jump out the window!

67
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:37,005
You`ve been my whole life
for two years. l can`t go back.

68
00:06:37,212 --> 00:06:39,305
You turned my life around!

69
00:06:39,515 --> 00:06:42,279
l never said l`d leave Miriam.

70
00:06:42,484 --> 00:06:45,920
``There`s no passion left.``
Those are your words...

71
00:06:46,121 --> 00:06:49,955
...unless you lied.
Or there`s something l don`t know.

72
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:54,459
-Have you met someone else?
-What? For God`s sake, Dolores.

73
00:06:54,697 --> 00:06:56,392
-Dolores--
-What?

74
00:06:56,632 --> 00:06:57,929
Now, look.

75
00:06:58,133 --> 00:07:02,229
l`ve lived with her 25 years.
The roots are very deep.

76
00:07:02,438 --> 00:07:04,497
l can`t go on leading two lives.

77
00:07:04,707 --> 00:07:09,303
You`re not doing her a favor by
pretending. l won`t be without you.

78
00:07:09,511 --> 00:07:13,607
This won`t happen without a fight!
l wanna speak to Miriam!

79
00:07:13,816 --> 00:07:15,807
-Nothing`s happening, okay?
-No!

80
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:18,384
Yes! Listen to me, please.

81
00:07:18,587 --> 00:07:22,648
We`ll work something out.
Let me get my thoughts together.

82
00:07:22,858 --> 00:07:25,019
Just don`t do anything rash.

83
00:07:25,227 --> 00:07:26,592
Dolores.

84
00:07:28,464 --> 00:07:29,488
What?

85
00:07:33,001 --> 00:07:34,593
lt`s gonna be okay.

86
00:07:37,372 --> 00:07:38,999
Oh, God.

87
00:07:40,175 --> 00:07:41,767
-You were gonna wait--
-Annie--

88
00:07:41,977 --> 00:07:44,844
-Then throw me aside!
-Don`t dramatize,

89
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:49,108
I`ve given you the best years
of my life!

90
00:07:49,318 --> 00:07:50,376
Get out of here!

91
00:07:50,586 --> 00:07:53,282
I know what you are,
Lucky I found out!

92
00:07:53,489 --> 00:07:55,514
Those are my clothes!

93
00:07:59,128 --> 00:08:00,425
That was great.

94
00:08:00,629 --> 00:08:03,462
-The tuxedos, the evening gowns.
-Great.

95
00:08:03,665 --> 00:08:07,101
lt was wonderful to live like that.
This is awful.

96
00:08:07,302 --> 00:08:10,396
Let me get a cab. You stay here.

97
00:08:10,606 --> 00:08:14,508
-You wanna see a movie again tomorrow?
-Sure, Uncle Cliff.

98
00:08:14,710 --> 00:08:15,699
Jesus.

99
00:08:15,911 --> 00:08:19,005
Unless maybe we should
make it a museum day.

100
00:08:19,214 --> 00:08:24,117
l promised your dad on his deathbed
you`d get a well-rounded education.

101
00:08:24,319 --> 00:08:28,050
We probably shouldn`t
go to the movies every day...

102
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:29,884
...even though l`d love to.

103
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:32,060
While we wait for a cab...

104
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:34,821
...l`ll give you
your lesson for today.

105
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,554
Your lesson is this:

106
00:08:36,765 --> 00:08:39,495
Don`t listen to what
your teachers say.

107
00:08:39,701 --> 00:08:41,794
Just see what they look like.

108
00:08:42,004 --> 00:08:45,235
Then you`ll know what life
will really be like.

109
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:48,637
You heard it here first.
l see a cab. lf we run...

110
00:08:48,844 --> 00:08:52,569
...we can kick the crutch
from that old lady and get it.

111
00:08:54,604 --> 00:08:57,300
-l`m back!
-Where were you?

112
00:08:57,507 --> 00:09:01,603
-Just out and around.
-Took your niece to a movie again.

113
00:09:01,811 --> 00:09:04,974
l`m crazy about that kid.
She`s just great.

114
00:09:05,181 --> 00:09:08,878
My brother`s in town.
He asked us to a dinner party.

115
00:09:09,085 --> 00:09:12,452
-Jesus.
-Please. You gonna make another scene?

116
00:09:12,655 --> 00:09:16,853
-l didn`t do that last time.
-You did. Your resentment showed.

117
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:22,327
l don`t resent him. He`s a pompous ass.
You don`t see it since you love him.

118
00:09:22,532 --> 00:09:24,193
-What did you say?
-Nothing.

119
00:09:24,401 --> 00:09:26,892
You did. You`re running down Lester.

120
00:09:27,103 --> 00:09:30,561
-l like your brother Ben.
-You`re not jealous of him.

121
00:09:30,774 --> 00:09:33,607
l`m jealous because
he`s a TV producer?

122
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:37,610
No. Because he`s highly respected
and he`s a millionaire...

123
00:09:37,814 --> 00:09:40,180
...and doing what you`d like to do.

124
00:09:40,383 --> 00:09:43,841
Listen, l can`t watch his stuff.
lt`s submental.

125
00:09:44,054 --> 00:09:47,785
-He wants to talk to you about a job.
-l don`t need one.

126
00:09:47,991 --> 00:09:50,459
Didn`t l get honorable mention at--?

127
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:53,561
The Cincinnati Documentary
Film Festival?

128
00:09:53,763 --> 00:09:57,426
Everybody got honorable mention
who showed up.

129
00:09:57,634 --> 00:10:00,660
Boy, things have really
changed around here.

130
00:10:09,179 --> 00:10:11,409
Wendy, Cliff, meet Lisa.

131
00:10:11,614 --> 00:10:14,777
My sister, Wendy.
My brother-in-law, Clifford.

132
00:10:14,984 --> 00:10:18,784
-Lisa`s starring in my new series.
-Not really starring.

133
00:10:18,988 --> 00:10:22,651
You`re one of the stars.
lt`s an ensemble piece.

134
00:10:22,859 --> 00:10:25,225
-Hello, Lester.
-Hello, darling.

135
00:10:25,428 --> 00:10:28,591
-So glad you came.
-Thank you for inviting me.

136
00:10:28,798 --> 00:10:32,029
Have a drink. l`ll be right there.

137
00:10:32,235 --> 00:10:35,898
She gave a bundle to
The Museum of Broadcasting.

138
00:10:36,739 --> 00:10:40,140
-She plays a--
-A lawyer for the ACLU.

139
00:10:40,343 --> 00:10:42,868
Married to a conservative writer.

140
00:10:43,079 --> 00:10:46,412
-So we can get into issues.
-We`ll try to be fair.

141
00:10:46,616 --> 00:10:49,949
But knowing Lester,
he`ll slant it to the left.

142
00:10:50,153 --> 00:10:51,177
Let`s hope so.

143
00:10:51,387 --> 00:10:53,855
-We`re shooting here.
-You`ll be here?

144
00:10:54,057 --> 00:10:56,321
l wanna shoot more in New York.

145
00:10:56,526 --> 00:10:58,460
-Oh, great.
-l love this town.

146
00:10:58,661 --> 00:11:01,789
Out there is such
a Mickey Mouse environment.

147
00:11:01,998 --> 00:11:03,397
The reason l`m here--

148
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:07,263
-Hello, Lester.
-l wanna talk to you. Don`t go away.

149
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:10,598
A bunch of us are getting together...

150
00:11:10,807 --> 00:11:13,537
...to build a studio here in the city.

151
00:11:13,743 --> 00:11:17,042
ln fact-- l`m sorry,
just give me one second.

152
00:11:17,247 --> 00:11:18,680
ldea for series:

153
00:11:18,882 --> 00:11:22,215
A high-profile builder,
with grandiose dreams...

154
00:11:22,418 --> 00:11:25,387
...a lá Donald Trump.
Shot in New York.

155
00:11:25,588 --> 00:11:28,386
-Look who`s here.
-That`s my brother Ben.

156
00:11:28,591 --> 00:11:32,118
Ben, Carol, come here.
Hi, kid. Nice to see you.

157
00:11:33,029 --> 00:11:34,690
-Hi, honey.
-Hi, sweetheart.

158
00:11:34,898 --> 00:11:37,992
-Hi, Cliff.
-How you doing? How are your eyes?

159
00:11:38,201 --> 00:11:40,999
Not so good. lt`s not so optimistic.

160
00:11:41,204 --> 00:11:43,468
l`ve been seeing Dr. Rosenthal.

161
00:11:43,673 --> 00:11:46,642
Lester, don`t you want
to talk to Clifford?

162
00:11:46,843 --> 00:11:49,437
Oh, yeah. Step into my office.

163
00:11:50,847 --> 00:11:54,078
-Hi, l`m Lisa.
-Hi. We didn`t meet. l`m sorry.

164
00:11:54,284 --> 00:11:57,720
-So are you in TV too?
-No.

165
00:11:57,921 --> 00:11:59,752
No. l`m a rabbi.

166
00:12:00,557 --> 00:12:03,424
You don`t wear an outfit or anything?

167
00:12:03,993 --> 00:12:06,985
Public television wants to do
a documentary...

168
00:12:07,197 --> 00:12:09,495
...on the way l talk and think--

169
00:12:09,699 --> 00:12:12,896
lt`s part of their
Creative Mind series.

170
00:12:13,102 --> 00:12:15,400
So l told them about you.

171
00:12:15,605 --> 00:12:18,267
Thanks. l`m working on my own thing.

172
00:12:18,474 --> 00:12:20,499
-A little film.
-Wendy told me.

173
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:25,238
A film about some philosophy
professor, which is admirable.

174
00:12:25,448 --> 00:12:30,078
But this is a chance to earn
decent money, reach a big audience.

175
00:12:30,286 --> 00:12:33,380
Last thing you need
is me as your biographer.

176
00:12:33,590 --> 00:12:37,959
l make these little films on
toxic waste and starving children.

177
00:12:38,161 --> 00:12:42,757
l`ll be frank. You`re not my
first choice. lt`s a favor to Wendy.

178
00:12:42,966 --> 00:12:47,733
-You never work. She`s embarrassed.
-l`ve worked, but nobody pays me.

179
00:12:47,937 --> 00:12:50,462
l know you don`t respect what l do.

180
00:12:50,673 --> 00:12:53,107
But l got a closet full of Emmys.

181
00:12:53,309 --> 00:12:56,506
You think that`s bullshit.
Fine. l understand.

182
00:12:56,713 --> 00:13:00,205
Maybe l could use the money
to finish my movie.

183
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,111
l do have some debts.

184
00:13:02,318 --> 00:13:03,683
ldea for farce:

185
00:13:03,886 --> 00:13:08,220
A poor loser agrees to do
the story of a great man`s life.

186
00:13:08,424 --> 00:13:11,359
And in the process,
he learns deep values.

187
00:13:14,597 --> 00:13:18,533
-What takes you to Boston?
-I`m lecturing at a symposium,

188
00:13:18,735 --> 00:13:21,135
lncidentally, my name`s Dolores.

189
00:13:21,337 --> 00:13:23,032
-Hello, Dolores.
-Hello.

190
00:13:23,239 --> 00:13:25,332
-Pretty name.
-Thank you.

191
00:13:25,975 --> 00:13:29,342
-Do you go to Boston often?
-Not very often,

192
00:13:29,545 --> 00:13:32,343
I don`t know anyone
in Boston, actually,

193
00:13:32,548 --> 00:13:33,981
-Really?
-Yeah,

194
00:13:42,358 --> 00:13:43,347
-Morning.
-Hi.

195
00:13:43,559 --> 00:13:46,528
A Miss Paley called,
said it was urgent.

196
00:13:52,669 --> 00:13:56,537
Why did you phone me?
l told you l`d call you.

197
00:13:56,739 --> 00:14:00,766
l couldn`t help it.
l was going out of my skin.

198
00:14:02,712 --> 00:14:04,680
l have to see you later.

199
00:14:05,081 --> 00:14:06,605
l have to!

200
00:14:08,051 --> 00:14:09,177
Okay.

201
00:14:10,186 --> 00:14:12,086
After work is okay.

202
00:14:15,358 --> 00:14:16,552
l see it.

203
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,749
Yeah.

204
00:14:19,762 --> 00:14:21,024
l see it.

205
00:14:22,465 --> 00:14:24,399
Oh, God.

206
00:14:25,168 --> 00:14:26,328
What?

207
00:14:27,804 --> 00:14:29,704
l need to take a minute.

208
00:14:32,108 --> 00:14:33,575
What`s wrong, Judah?

209
00:14:35,111 --> 00:14:37,204
l`m in such trouble, Ben.

210
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,811
What is it?

211
00:14:39,882 --> 00:14:42,009
l need to talk to someone.

212
00:14:42,552 --> 00:14:43,678
Sure.

213
00:14:45,054 --> 00:14:48,956
l`ve known you for years.
You`re religious. l`m not.

214
00:14:49,158 --> 00:14:52,958
We`ve differed on many points,
but l do respect you.

215
00:14:53,730 --> 00:14:56,665
-May l confide in you?
-Of course.

216
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,094
Go ahead. Everything`s confidential.

217
00:15:04,407 --> 00:15:06,637
l`ve done a foolish thing.

218
00:15:06,843 --> 00:15:08,640
Senseless. Vain.

219
00:15:08,845 --> 00:15:10,039
Dumb.

220
00:15:13,549 --> 00:15:15,107
Another woman.

221
00:15:19,522 --> 00:15:23,925
Maybe l was flattered, vulnerable.

222
00:15:24,127 --> 00:15:26,857
Maybe because she was
helpless and alone.

223
00:15:27,063 --> 00:15:29,964
But now my life`s
about to go up in smoke.

224
00:15:30,466 --> 00:15:34,027
-Can`t you break it off?
-The woman won`t allow it.

225
00:15:34,537 --> 00:15:37,370
She`s young. She`s very unstable.

226
00:15:37,573 --> 00:15:39,097
She`s an hysteric.

227
00:15:39,475 --> 00:15:41,033
And vindictive.

228
00:15:41,277 --> 00:15:42,835
And it`s my fault.

229
00:15:43,045 --> 00:15:46,105
l instigated it. l prolonged it.

230
00:15:46,315 --> 00:15:49,409
l tried to back off,
but l was too weak.

231
00:15:49,619 --> 00:15:52,213
But l promised her nothing.

232
00:15:52,422 --> 00:15:55,220
But did l? l don`t even know anymore.

233
00:15:55,425 --> 00:15:58,417
ln the heat of passion,
you say things.

234
00:15:58,628 --> 00:16:01,825
After two years of living
this double life...

235
00:16:02,031 --> 00:16:04,295
...l awakened as if from a dream...

236
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:08,300
-...and realized what l`d be losing.
-lt`s called wisdom.

237
00:16:08,504 --> 00:16:10,631
lt comes to some suddenly.

238
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:14,833
We realize the difference between
what`s deep and lasting...

239
00:16:15,044 --> 00:16:18,377
...versus the superficial
payoff of the moment.

