00:40:45,845 --> 00:40:48,370
,,,a moral structure
with real meaning,,,

613
00:40:48,581 --> 00:40:52,347
,,,and forgiveness
and some higher power,

614
00:40:52,552 --> 00:40:55,953
Otherwise, there`s no basis
to know how to live,

615
00:40:56,155 --> 00:40:58,646
And I know a spark of that notion,,,

616
00:40:58,858 --> 00:41:01,088
,,,is inside you somewhere too,

617
00:41:06,899 --> 00:41:09,367
Could you really go through with it?

618
00:41:11,971 --> 00:41:14,303
What choice do l have, man?

619
00:41:14,574 --> 00:41:16,041
Tell me.

620
00:41:16,943 --> 00:41:20,435
Give the people you`ve hurt
a chance to forgive you.

621
00:41:20,947 --> 00:41:23,142
Miriam won`t forgive me.

622
00:41:23,449 --> 00:41:25,246
She`ll be broken.

623
00:41:25,618 --> 00:41:27,586
She worships me.

624
00:41:28,221 --> 00:41:33,124
She`ll be humiliated before everyone.
This woman plans to make a stink.

625
00:41:34,394 --> 00:41:37,693
-Did you make promises to her?
-No.

626
00:41:38,564 --> 00:41:41,556
Maybe l led her on
more than l realized.

627
00:41:41,768 --> 00:41:44,293
She`s so emotionally hungry.

628
00:41:44,771 --> 00:41:49,367
-But it`s deeper than just Miriam.
-Meaning financial improprieties?

629
00:41:49,675 --> 00:41:51,006
No.

630
00:41:52,211 --> 00:41:53,838
Maybe l--

631
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:57,340
Maybe l did make
some questionable moves.

632
00:42:01,354 --> 00:42:03,652
Only you would know that, Judah.

633
00:42:03,923 --> 00:42:06,118
l don`t anymore, Ben.

634
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:10,789
Sometimes it`s worse than--
Worse than jail.

635
00:42:12,031 --> 00:42:14,192
lt`s a human life.

636
00:42:15,401 --> 00:42:17,596
You don`t think God sees?

637
00:42:19,505 --> 00:42:24,568
-God is a luxury l can`t afford.
-Now you`re talking like your brother.

638
00:42:26,045 --> 00:42:28,411
Jack lives in the real world.

639
00:42:28,614 --> 00:42:31,174
You live in the kingdom of heaven.

640
00:42:32,385 --> 00:42:35,479
l managed to keep free
of that real world...

641
00:42:35,688 --> 00:42:38,088
...but suddenly, it`s found me.

642
00:42:38,624 --> 00:42:42,754
You fool around with her,
then when you think it`s enough...

643
00:42:42,962 --> 00:42:45,396
...you wanna sweep her under the rug?

644
00:42:46,165 --> 00:42:49,328
There`s no other solution but Jack`s.

645
00:42:49,902 --> 00:42:53,338
l push one button
and l can sleep again nights.

646
00:42:53,539 --> 00:42:55,439
Could you sleep with that?

647
00:42:56,943 --> 00:42:59,104
ls that who you really are?

648
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:04,611
l will not be destroyed
by this neurotic woman.

649
00:43:06,452 --> 00:43:08,511
But the law.

650
00:43:10,022 --> 00:43:12,855
Without the law, it`s all darkness.

651
00:43:14,727 --> 00:43:16,854
You sound like my father.

652
00:43:17,430 --> 00:43:21,924
What good is the law if it
prevents me from receiving justice?

653
00:43:22,735 --> 00:43:26,899
ls what she`s doing to me just?
ls this what l deserve?

654
00:43:39,619 --> 00:43:42,087
Jack? lt`s Judah.

655
00:43:43,589 --> 00:43:46,717
We should move ahead
with what we discussed.

656
00:43:48,294 --> 00:43:50,262
How much will you need?

657
00:44:12,065 --> 00:44:13,862
lt`s not funny, guys.

658
00:44:14,067 --> 00:44:17,969
You`re not thinking funny.
You gotta think with your ear.

659
00:44:18,171 --> 00:44:22,301
Do you understand?
Here`s the difference. lt`s very easy.

660
00:44:22,509 --> 00:44:27,412
lf it bends, it`s funny.
lf it breaks, it`s not funny.

661
00:44:27,614 --> 00:44:32,210
lt`s very simple. Wait a minute.
Jeff, this is Alva.

662
00:44:32,419 --> 00:44:35,946
-Hi, pleased to meet you.
-Don`t shoot this part.

663
00:44:37,190 --> 00:44:40,489
Alva`s in the new series.
l don`t know what part...

664
00:44:40,694 --> 00:44:44,528
...l just know l want her.
lt`s wonderful. You look great.

665
00:44:44,731 --> 00:44:47,996
Trust me, they love you. Be right out.

666
00:44:48,735 --> 00:44:51,795
Don`t do that while we`re shooting.

667
00:44:52,005 --> 00:44:55,736
Do you understand?
Think of Oedipus. Oedipus is funny.

668
00:44:55,942 --> 00:44:58,103
That`s the structure of funny.

669
00:44:58,311 --> 00:45:03,374
``Who did this terrible thing?
My God, it was me.`` That`s funny--

670
00:45:03,583 --> 00:45:06,984
Don`t do it, they`re shooting!
What are you doing?

671
00:45:08,621 --> 00:45:13,422
You will notice
that what we are aiming at,,,

672
00:45:13,827 --> 00:45:17,593
,,,when we fall in love
is a very strange paradox,

673
00:45:17,797 --> 00:45:22,166
The paradox consists of the fact
that when we fall in love,,,

674
00:45:22,369 --> 00:45:25,861
,,,we are seeking to re-find,,,

675
00:45:26,072 --> 00:45:28,472
,,,all or some of the people,,,

676
00:45:28,675 --> 00:45:31,371
,,, to whom we were attached
as children,

677
00:45:31,578 --> 00:45:35,207
On the other hand,
we ask our beloved,,,

678
00:45:35,415 --> 00:45:38,578
,,, to correct all of the wrongs,,,

679
00:45:38,785 --> 00:45:44,087
,,, that these early parents
or siblings inflicted upon us,

680
00:45:44,290 --> 00:45:47,350
So love contains
in it the contradiction,,,

681
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:50,188
,,, the attempt to return
to the past,,,

682
00:45:50,397 --> 00:45:53,855
,,,and the attempt to undo the past,

683
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:57,701
See? No limos, no bimbos,
no awards or anything.

684
00:45:57,904 --> 00:46:03,137
-This guy is a thinker, an intellect.
-When you ultimately show this...

685
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:08,576
...to the people that make the
decision, emphasize his view of life.

686
00:46:08,782 --> 00:46:13,549
-lt`s life-affirming. They`d love it.
-This is what l need.

687
00:46:13,753 --> 00:46:18,918
A little interest in my work,
a little encouragement or something.

688
00:46:19,125 --> 00:46:23,027
l got a bottle of champagne
as a prize from Paris.

689
00:46:23,229 --> 00:46:28,030
l got honorable mention
for a documentary l did on leukemia.

690
00:46:28,234 --> 00:46:32,898
-Want some champagne?
-l never say no to champagne or caviar.

691
00:46:33,106 --> 00:46:38,237
Perfect, l have no caviar. l have
oat bran. lt`s better for your heart.

692
00:46:40,814 --> 00:46:44,306
He was very eloquent
on the subject of love.

693
00:46:44,517 --> 00:46:47,748
Yeah. Wish l had read him
before l got married.

694
00:46:47,954 --> 00:46:51,651
-lt would`ve saved my gall bladder.
-What did you say?

695
00:46:51,858 --> 00:46:56,659
Nothing. He wrote an interesting
book on human relationships.

696
00:46:56,863 --> 00:47:00,060
He speaks very highly
of love at first sight.

697
00:47:00,266 --> 00:47:03,292
l fell for my ex-husband
at first sight.

698
00:47:03,503 --> 00:47:05,869
l should`ve taken a second look.

699
00:47:06,072 --> 00:47:09,166
Actually, it was my fault
as much as his.

700
00:47:09,375 --> 00:47:12,344
You still wear a wedding ring.
Why is that?

701
00:47:12,545 --> 00:47:17,278
Well, l guess l`m just
not ready to take it off.

702
00:47:17,617 --> 00:47:21,178
lt`s good. lt keeps me
from getting asked out.

703
00:47:21,387 --> 00:47:25,187
You must have had a terrible
marriage to avoid dating.

704
00:47:25,391 --> 00:47:30,090
Well, no. He was great,
very brilliant. He`s an architect.

705
00:47:30,296 --> 00:47:32,924
But if you`re gonna have an affair...

