-She hasn`t gone back.

780
00:54:38,527 --> 00:54:42,520
ls everything okay, sweetheart?
You look kind of upset.

781
00:54:42,731 --> 00:54:45,097
Yeah, l`m fine. lt`s just Jack.

782
00:54:45,434 --> 00:54:49,063
She`s still wearing that collar
when she drives.

783
00:54:49,271 --> 00:54:51,569
Well, sometimes it does work.

784
00:54:52,341 --> 00:54:55,242
We were talking about
Oriental medicine.

785
00:54:55,444 --> 00:54:59,847
A friend consulted a Chinese physician
with an eye problem.

786
00:55:00,049 --> 00:55:03,109
He inserted a cat whisker
into her tear duct.

787
00:55:03,319 --> 00:55:07,119
She`s been telling the story
all week. lt`s her favorite.

788
00:55:07,323 --> 00:55:09,154
-What happened?
-lt cured her.

789
00:55:09,358 --> 00:55:13,488
-lt did.
-You told me he uses wires too.

790
00:55:13,696 --> 00:55:14,685
Why would you--?

791
00:55:14,897 --> 00:55:18,025
-ln acupuncture, you use needles.
-But very fine.

792
00:55:18,234 --> 00:55:22,170
-But that`s a different procedure.
-What do you think?

793
00:55:25,474 --> 00:55:27,533
Judah, what do you think?

794
00:55:27,743 --> 00:55:31,907
l think l`ve done a terrible thing.

795
00:55:32,381 --> 00:55:34,110
What`s wrong, honey?

796
00:55:35,451 --> 00:55:38,682
l left these papers at the office...

797
00:55:38,888 --> 00:55:41,448
...which l absolutely need tonight.

798
00:55:41,657 --> 00:55:45,855
l can`t believe l did this.
How negligent of me.

799
00:55:46,061 --> 00:55:48,586
l have a conference in the morning.

800
00:55:48,797 --> 00:55:53,291
-You`re not going tonight.
-l must. l have an hour`s work to do.

801
00:55:53,502 --> 00:55:56,130
-But we`re having a party.
-l`m so sorry.

802
00:55:56,338 --> 00:55:59,830
-Please forgive me. l--
-Don`t apologize.

803
00:56:00,042 --> 00:56:02,602
l don`t like him driving at night.

804
00:56:02,811 --> 00:56:07,145
-Stanley, l`m so sorry about this.
-Chris, would you go with him?

805
00:56:07,349 --> 00:56:09,715
-Would you like some company?
-No.

806
00:56:09,919 --> 00:56:12,444
Darling, forgive me. l must go.

807
00:56:12,655 --> 00:56:15,123
lt was a wonderful evening.

808
00:56:15,324 --> 00:56:17,952
lf you`re here when l get back--

809
00:56:18,160 --> 00:56:21,721
-Don`t worry about us.
-l couldn`t apologize more.

810
00:56:21,931 --> 00:56:24,559
Let`s just finish the coffee.
Sit down.

811
00:56:24,767 --> 00:56:26,166
He`ll be back.

812
00:58:37,166 --> 00:58:38,861
I`ll say it once again,

813
00:58:39,535 --> 00:58:42,527
The eyes of God see all.

814
00:58:43,172 --> 00:58:47,734
Listen, Judah. There is absolutely
nothing that escapes his sight.

815
00:58:47,943 --> 00:58:50,935
He sees the righteous and the wicked.

816
00:58:51,146 --> 00:58:53,706
And the righteous will be rewarded...

817
00:58:53,916 --> 00:58:58,478
...but the wicked will be
punished for eternity.

818
01:00:22,538 --> 01:00:23,766
Hello?

819
01:01:02,411 --> 01:01:06,142
l want your opinion.
l`m doing a special show on jazz.

820
01:01:06,348 --> 01:01:08,339
l admire her opinion so.

821
01:01:08,550 --> 01:01:12,179
Did you tell them l want
to produce an idea you have?

822
01:01:12,387 --> 01:01:16,118
She wants to do a different
Chekhov story every month.

823
01:01:16,325 --> 01:01:18,759
-He wrote a million.
-That`s sweet.

824
01:01:18,961 --> 01:01:22,795
-l`m putty in your hands.
-What will l do with putty?

825
01:01:22,998 --> 01:01:26,695
She`s always got a zinger.
This vixen, this minx.

826
01:01:26,902 --> 01:01:31,396
We should really be going.
We have to pick up those airsick bags.

827
01:01:31,607 --> 01:01:36,909
l gotta get up to teach Emily Dickinson
to upper middle-class crack addicts.

828
01:01:37,112 --> 01:01:38,315
-One of my favorite poets.
-Me too.

829
01:01:38,315 --> 01:01:39,475
-One of my favorite poets.
-Me too.

830
01:01:39,683 --> 01:01:43,585
-``Because l could not stop for death.``
-``He kindly stopped for me.``

831
01:01:43,787 --> 01:01:45,379
The word ``kindly,`` right?

832
01:01:45,589 --> 01:01:49,252
``The carriage held but just ourselves
and immortality.``

833
01:01:49,459 --> 01:01:51,689
``We slowly drove, he knew no haste.``

834
01:01:51,895 --> 01:01:54,261
``l had put away
my labor, and my leisure too...``

835
01:01:54,464 --> 01:01:55,556
``...for his civility.``

836
01:01:55,766 --> 01:01:59,566
-He was a great English student.
-Not that l graduated.

837
01:01:59,770 --> 01:02:03,672
l couldn`t graduate, but now
my school teaches a class in...

838
01:02:03,874 --> 01:02:07,640
-...existential motifs in my sitcoms.
-Really?

839
01:02:08,445 --> 01:02:10,538
-Where did you study?
-Columbia.

840
01:02:10,747 --> 01:02:13,682
Columbia? What did you major in?

841
01:02:13,884 --> 01:02:16,444
Law. l graduated from the law school.

842
01:02:16,653 --> 01:02:21,090
-You didn`t practice?
-l did. But then l met my husband.

843
01:02:21,291 --> 01:02:26,228
We moved to Europe for a while.
lt`s a long, boring story.

844
01:02:26,429 --> 01:02:28,863
l wish you`d go back to your job.

845
01:02:29,065 --> 01:02:33,593
l used to edit newsreel footage.
Floods, fires and famines.

846
01:02:33,804 --> 01:02:34,793
Depressing.

847
01:02:35,005 --> 01:02:38,168
-We don`t all have to go.
-No. l do.

848
01:02:38,375 --> 01:02:41,606
We`ll go. You two stay
and talk business.

849
01:02:41,812 --> 01:02:44,645
-l could go too, if you`d like.
-Let`s go.

850
01:02:44,848 --> 01:02:48,113
-Let`s go for a drink.
-l wouldn`t mind.

851
01:02:48,318 --> 01:02:51,617
-l`m just exhausted.
-From what? lt`s early.

852
01:02:51,822 --> 01:02:53,016
Some other time.

853
01:02:53,223 --> 01:02:56,420
-One little drink.
-Really. Some other time.

854
01:02:58,028 --> 01:02:59,962
Lester was so pushy tonight.

855
01:03:00,163 --> 01:03:03,826
