but he`s after her.

856
01:03:04,034 --> 01:03:08,767
-She really likes him. l can tell.
-You`re kidding. She likes him?

857
01:03:08,972 --> 01:03:12,931
What`s not to like?
He`s attractive, rich, charming.

858
01:03:13,143 --> 01:03:16,579
You`re prejudiced.
She put him down pretty good.

859
01:03:16,780 --> 01:03:20,272
He said, ``One drink.``
She said, ``Some other time.``

860
01:03:20,483 --> 01:03:22,747
l loved that. Socked it to him.

861
01:03:22,953 --> 01:03:26,047
-Fine. Enough.
-That was pretty witty.

862
01:03:26,256 --> 01:03:31,023
-How can you say she likes him?
-She was staring at him all night.

863
01:03:31,228 --> 01:03:36,291
-She probably can`t believe her eyes.
-You wouldn`t pick up on those things.

864
01:03:36,499 --> 01:03:39,195
You`re not the least bit romantic.

865
01:03:39,402 --> 01:03:42,633
You`re the one who stopped
sleeping with me.

866
01:03:42,839 --> 01:03:47,037
lt`ll be a year on April 20th.
Same date as Hitler`s birthday.

867
01:03:47,244 --> 01:03:49,906
l`m not discussing that anymore.

868
01:03:50,113 --> 01:03:52,946
l`ll bet you she`s with him now.

869
01:03:53,149 --> 01:03:56,050
For how much?
l`m serious. For how much?

870
01:03:56,253 --> 01:03:58,915
You really know how to get my goat.

871
01:04:24,281 --> 01:04:26,374
Hi. lt`s Clifford.

872
01:04:26,683 --> 01:04:29,516
Yes. l knew you`d be in.

873
01:04:30,287 --> 01:04:33,814
Tonight was a lot of fun.
Wasn`t Lester so silly?

874
01:04:34,024 --> 01:04:37,460
He`s so self-important.
He was pushing all night.

875
01:04:37,661 --> 01:04:40,186
l was frankly embarrassed for him.

876
01:04:43,833 --> 01:04:45,994
What is he doing there?

877
01:04:49,005 --> 01:04:52,065
You`re talking business at midnight?

878
01:04:54,811 --> 01:04:58,838
That could be very dangerous.
You want me to come over?

879
01:05:02,819 --> 01:05:05,515
Okay, if you can handle it.

880
01:05:06,923 --> 01:05:09,756
Okay. l`ll see you tomorrow.

881
01:05:18,635 --> 01:05:20,330
l`m in love with Halley.

882
01:05:20,537 --> 01:05:23,267
Lester is making his move.
l can see it.

883
01:05:23,473 --> 01:05:25,873
He wants her just for a conquest.

884
01:05:26,076 --> 01:05:28,874
lt`s so shallow,
and l`m crazy about her.

885
01:05:29,079 --> 01:05:32,446
l can`t compete with a guy
who`s rich and famous.

886
01:05:32,649 --> 01:05:37,018
-He`s no competition for you.
-God bless you for saying that.

887
01:05:37,220 --> 01:05:39,085
But you`ll find out...

888
01:05:39,289 --> 01:05:44,226
...that great depth and smoldering
sensuality doesn`t always win.

889
01:05:44,527 --> 01:05:47,087
You know his brother Ben the rabbi?

890
01:05:47,297 --> 01:05:50,425
He`s a wonderful guy.
He`s going blind.

891
01:05:50,633 --> 01:05:55,195
He`s got a terrible eye disease.
He`ll be blind in a few months.

892
01:05:55,405 --> 01:05:58,533
He has a great attitude.
He`s really a mensch.

893
01:05:59,776 --> 01:06:01,505
All right. Look left.

894
01:06:02,645 --> 01:06:04,636
Now straight ahead, Ben.

895
01:06:06,883 --> 01:06:08,350
Now to the right.

896
01:06:09,352 --> 01:06:10,614
That`s good.

897
01:06:18,595 --> 01:06:19,619
My mother said,,,

898
01:06:21,164 --> 01:06:23,598
...that l should go to the doctor.

899
01:06:24,234 --> 01:06:26,725
Because my eyes weren`t so good.

900
01:06:26,936 --> 01:06:29,427
Well, you`re an ophthalmologist.

901
01:06:29,639 --> 01:06:32,972
Do you agree the eyes
are the windows of the soul?

902
01:06:33,176 --> 01:06:37,237
l believe they`re windows.
l`m not sure they see the soul.

903
01:06:37,447 --> 01:06:40,007
My mother taught me l have a soul.

904
01:06:40,216 --> 01:06:43,151
And it will live on after l`m gone.

905
01:06:43,353 --> 01:06:47,949
lf you look deeply enough in my eyes,
you can see it.

906
01:06:52,162 --> 01:06:54,062
So, what`s the verdict?

907
01:06:54,697 --> 01:06:58,292
l want to resolve this
before my daughter`s wedding.

908
01:06:59,736 --> 01:07:03,695
-Julie`s getting married?
-Time passes quickly, doesn`t it?

909
01:07:03,907 --> 01:07:07,206
Remember she was just a baby?
Well, yours too.

910
01:07:10,613 --> 01:07:13,912
Are you okay, Judah?
You don`t look so good.

911
01:07:14,117 --> 01:07:17,348
l just haven`t been
sleeping that well.

912
01:07:17,921 --> 01:07:20,116
Tell me, if l`m not prying...

913
01:07:20,323 --> 01:07:23,724
...did you ever resolve
your personal difficulties?

914
01:07:24,594 --> 01:07:29,429
Yes, actually. lt resolved itself.
The woman listened to reason.

915
01:07:29,632 --> 01:07:31,065
Did she?

916
01:07:31,768 --> 01:07:34,532
That`s wonderful. So you got a break.

917
01:07:34,871 --> 01:07:39,331
Sometimes, to have a little good luck
is the most brilliant plan.

918
01:07:39,676 --> 01:07:43,612
Relax. You`re white.
You`re gonna have a breakdown.

919
01:07:43,813 --> 01:07:48,011
You expect me to be my old self?
l jump when the phone rings.

920
01:07:48,785 --> 01:07:52,881
-No good can come of this.
-l kept you uninvolved.

921
01:07:53,089 --> 01:07:56,547
The guy who`s responsible
is back in New Orleans.

922
01:07:56,759 --> 01:07:58,727
lt`s pure evil, Jack.

923
01:07:59,229 --> 01:08:03,188
A man kills for money.
He doesn`t even know his victims.

924
01:08:03,399 --> 01:08:06,698
He kills, you pay him
and he kills again.

925
01:08:06,903 --> 01:08:09,064
What was your alternative?

926
01:08:09,772 --> 01:08:11,967
How did l get in so deep?

927
01:08:13,510 --> 01:08:15,637
What dream was l following?

928
01:08:16,312 --> 01:08:20,942
You said it yourself a million times,
``You only go around once.``

929
01:08:22,118 --> 01:08:24,609
l went to her place after.

930
01:08:24,821 --> 01:08:27,813
l had to retrieve
some incriminating things.

931
01:08:28,791 --> 01:08:30,315
l saw her there.

932
01:08:31,394 --> 01:08:32,918
Just staring up...

933
01:08:33,129 --> 01:08:35,097
...an inert object.

934
01:08:36,266 --> 01:08:38,826
There was nothing behind her eyes.

935
01:08:39,035 --> 01:08:41,833
lf you looked into them,
all you saw was...

936
01:08:42,605 --> 01:08:44,470
...a black void.

937
01:09:20,887 --> 01:09:22,377
Can l help you?

938
01:09:24,924 --> 01:09:27,518
l used to live in this house once.

939
01:09:27,727 --> 01:09:29,991
Really? When?

940
01:09:30,763 --> 01:09:32,230
Many years ago.

941
01:09:34,534 --> 01:09:38,436
My brother and l used to race
through these rooms.

942
01:09:38,905 --> 01:09:43,308
He was a wonderful kid.
We were very close in those days.

943
01:09:46,512 --> 01:09:50,141
My father had high hopes for him
but it never seemed...

944
01:09:50,350 --> 01:09:52,113
...to work out for him.

945
01:09:56,089 --> 01:09:58,319
Do you mind if l take a minute?

946
01:09:58,524 --> 01:10:01,584
Everything seems to be
flooding through me.

947
01:10:01,794 --> 01:10:03,284
Sure.

948
01:10:25,018 --> 01:10:27,543
Sol, get on with it, I`m hungry,

949
01:10:27,987 --> 01:10:31,423
-Do you mind, May?
-This is such mumbo jumbo.

950
01:10:31,624 --> 01:10:33,057
Bring on the food.

951
01:10:33,259 --> 01:10:35,887
l apologize for
my disrespectful sister.

952
01:10:36,095 --> 01:10:41,294
This is the 20th century. Don`t fill
their heads with superstition.

953
01:10:41,501 --> 01:10:43,696
The intellectual, the teacher.

954
01:10:43,903 --> 01:10:46,804
Spare us your Leninist philosophy
for once.

955
01:10:47,006 --> 01:10:49,634
lf you don`t obey,
God will punish you?

956
01:10:49,842 --> 01:10:52,811
-Not me. He punishes the wicked.
-Like Hitler?

957
01:10:53,012 --> 01:10:54,479
We`re having a Seder!

958
01:10:54,680 --> 01:10:57,808
Six million Jews killed,
they got away with it.

959
01:10:58,017 --> 01:11:01,077
-How`d they get away with it?
-Open your eyes!

960
01:11:01,287 --> 01:11:04,313
Six million Jews.
They got off with nothing.

961
01:11:04,524 --> 01:11:07,891
-How could men do such a thing?
-Might makes right.

962
01:11:08,094 --> 01:11:12,360
-Until the Americans--
-l don`t like this talk at Seder.

963
01:11:12,565 --> 01:11:13,827
Okay! All right!

964
01:11:14,033 --> 01:11:17,594
-I think this is interesting,
-Yeah, you do,

965
01:11:17,804 --> 01:11:19,601
There`s this joke,

966
01:11:19,806 --> 01:11:21,967
A prizefighter enters the ring.

967
01:11:22,175 --> 01:11:25,633
His brother asks the family priest
to pray for him.

968
01:11:25,845 --> 01:11:29,281
He said, ``Okay.
But if he can punch, it`ll help.``

969
01:11:29,482 --> 01:11:33,885
So you`re saying you challenge
the moral structure of everything?

970
01:11:34,087 --> 01:11:38,148
Moral structure? You use
that nonsense on your pupils?

971
01:11:38,357 --> 01:11:41,588
You don`t find human impulses
basically decent?

972
01:11:41,794 --> 01:11:46,356
-There`s basically nothing.
-A cynic, a nihilist. Back to Russia.

973
01:11:46,566 --> 01:11:49,933
Well, listen. l happen
to agree with May...

974
01:11:50,136 --> 01:11:52,195
...when it comes to mumbo jumbo.

975
01:11:52,405 --> 01:11:56,136
But you come to every Seder.
You pray in Hebrew.

976
01:11:56,342 --> 01:12:00,278
l go through the motions.
Like any ritual, it`s a habit.

977
01:12:00,480 --> 01:12:04,541
So you say there`s no morality
anywhere in the whole world?

978
01:12:04,750 --> 01:12:09,210
For those who want it, it`s there.
Nothing`s handed down in stone.

979
01:12:09,422 --> 01:12:11,515
Sol`s kind of faith is a gift.

980
01:12:11,724 --> 01:12:14,852
lt`s like an ear for music
or talent to draw.

981
01:12:15,061 --> 01:12:18,724
You use logic on him all day
and he still believes.

982
01:12:18,931 --> 01:12:22,924
-Must everything be logical?
-And if a man commits a crime?

983
01:12:23,136 --> 01:12:24,694
lf he--

984
01:12:24,904 --> 01:12:26,337
lf he kills?

985
01:12:27,473 --> 01:12:31,136
-ln some way, he`ll be punished.
-lf he`s caught, Sol.

986
01:12:31,344 --> 01:12:35,940
``What originates from a black deed
will blossom in a foul manner.``

987
01:12:36,149 --> 01:12:39,277
You`re relying too heavily
on the Bible.

988
01:12:39,485 --> 01:12:43,922
Whether it`s the Old Testament
or Shakespeare, murder will out.

989
01:12:44,123 --> 01:12:47,650
-Who said anything about murder?
-You did.

990
01:12:50,096 --> 01:12:51,427
Did l?

991
01:12:53,666 --> 01:12:56,601
l say, if he can do it
and get away with it...

992
01:12:56,802 --> 01:13:00,704
...and chooses not to be bothered
by ethics, he`s home free.

993
01:13:00,907 --> 01:13:03,637
History is written by the winners.

994
01:13:03,843 --> 01:13:07,574
Had the Nazis won,
future generations would understand...

995
01:13:07,780 --> 01:13:09,941
...World War ll quite differently.

996
01:13:10,149 --> 01:13:14,017
Your aunt is brilliant,
but she`s had an unhappy life.

997
01:13:14,220 --> 01:13:19,419
And if all your faith is wrong--
l mean, just what if? lf?

998
01:13:19,625 --> 01:13:22,753
l`ll still have a better life
than doubters.

999
01:13:22,962 --> 01:13:26,955
Wait a minute. Are you saying
you prefer God to the truth?

1000
01:13:27,166 --> 01:13:32,001
-l`ll always choose God over truth.
-l agree with him.

1001
01:13:32,638 --> 01:13:35,505
l say, what goes around comes around.

1002
01:13:40,613 --> 01:13:45,016
-You okay? l was worried. lt`s late.
-l had some business.

1003
01:13:45,218 --> 01:13:46,708
Mrs. Ames is waiting.

1004
01:13:46,919 --> 01:13:49,251
-Any messages?
-You got an odd one.

1005
01:13:49,455 --> 01:13:52,720
A Detective O`Donnell
wanted to talk to you.

1006
01:13:52,925 --> 01:13:57,487
l tried to ask him what about,
but he only wants to talk with you.

1007
01:14:17,316 --> 01:14:20,945
-lt`s not a great movie, but it`s fun.
-l liked it.

1008
01:14:21,153 --> 01:14:23,485
Maybe l want to be an actress.

1009
01:14:23,689 --> 01:14:28,592
l don`t want you to be an actress.
Be on the Supreme Court or a doctor.

1010
01:14:28,794 --> 01:14:30,921
Show business is dog-eat-dog.

1011
01:14:31,130 --> 01:14:36,067
lt`s worse than dog-eat-dog. lt`s
dog-doesn`t-return-other-dog`s-calls.

1012
01:14:36,269 --> 01:14:38,294
l should check my service.

1013
01:14:38,504 --> 01:14:41,302
l don`t know why.
l never have messages.

1014
01:14:41,507 --> 01:14:45,034
-l call, l hear the girls giggling.
-How`s Halley?

1015
01:14:45,244 --> 01:14:48,042
She`s great. l`m gonna make my move.

1016
01:14:48,247 --> 01:14:52,343
But l have this ethical dilemma
because l`m married.

1017
01:14:52,551 --> 01:14:55,520
Clifford Stern. Any messages?
Can you check?

1018
01:14:55,721 --> 01:14:58,656
My heart says one thing.
My head, another.

1019
01:14:58,858 --> 01:15:02,589
lt`s hard to get your heart
and head together in life.

1020
01:15:02,795 --> 01:15:05,764
ln my case, they`re not
even friendly. Yes?

1021
01:15:09,635 --> 01:15:11,068
Really?

1022
01:15:16,709 --> 01:15:18,142
No.

1023
01:15:20,680 --> 01:15:22,204
Okay. Thank you.

1024
01:15:25,751 --> 01:15:27,082
What`s wrong?

1025
01:15:30,389 --> 01:15:32,323
Professor Levy...

1026
01:15:32,658 --> 01:15:34,785
...committed suicide.

1027
01:15:36,028 --> 01:15:38,326
But we must always remember,,,

1028
01:15:38,531 --> 01:15:42,126
,,, that we--
When we are born,,,

1029
01:15:42,335 --> 01:15:44,963
,,,we need a great deal of love,,,

1030
01:15:45,171 --> 01:15:48,766
,,,in order to persuade us
to stay in life,

1031
01:15:48,974 --> 01:15:52,774
Once we get that love,
it usually lasts us,

1032
01:15:52,978 --> 01:15:55,606
But the universe is a cold place,

1033
01:15:55,815 --> 01:15:59,273
It`s we who invest it
with our feelings,

1034
01:15:59,485 --> 01:16:02,147
And under certain conditions,,,

1035
01:16:02,355 --> 01:16:05,950
,,,we feel that the thing
isn`t worth it anymore,

1036
01:16:06,158 --> 01:16:10,720
l came as soon as l heard. l thought
you wouldn`t want to be alone.

1037
01:16:10,930 --> 01:16:15,390
God, it`s been terrible. l called--
The guy was not sick at all.

1038
01:16:15,601 --> 01:16:19,264
He left a note that said,
``l`ve gone out the window.``

1039
01:16:19,472 --> 01:16:23,738
A major intellectual, and this
is his note. What does it mean?

1040
01:16:23,943 --> 01:16:25,410
He was a role model.

1041
01:16:25,611 --> 01:16:30,571
-You`d think he`d leave a decent note.
-Did he have family or anything?

1042
01:16:30,783 --> 01:16:35,652
They were killed in the war. lt`s
strange. He`s seen the worst in life.

1043
01:16:35,855 --> 01:16:40,019
He always said yes to life.
Now today he said no.

1044
01:16:40,226 --> 01:16:43,855
lmagine his students,
how shattered they will be.

1045
01:16:44,063 --> 01:16:48,022
Where l grew up, in Brooklyn,
nobody committed suicide.

1046
01:16:48,234 --> 01:16:52,534
-Everyone was too unhappy.
-This will put a damper on the show.

1047
01:16:52,738 --> 01:16:55,730
l got 600,000 feet of film
on this guy...

1048
01:16:55,941 --> 01:16:58,535
...and he`s telling how great life is.

1049
01:16:58,744 --> 01:17:01,474
l`ll cut it up,
use it for guitar picks.

1050
01:17:01,680 --> 01:17:04,615
l was thinking,
no matter how elaborate...

1051
01:17:04,817 --> 01:17:07,581
...a philosophical system
you work out...

1052
01:17:07,787 --> 01:17:11,188
...in the end,
it`s gotta be incomplete.

1053
01:17:11,390 --> 01:17:15,486
l`ve been so annoyed all day.
l`m sorry for seeming cranky.

1054
01:17:15,694 --> 01:17:20,188
No, l understand. l just thought
you might want some company.

1055
01:17:23,235 --> 01:17:25,135
No. Don`t do that.

1056
01:17:25,704 --> 01:17:28,639
lt`s something l`ve wanted
to do for weeks.

1057
01:17:28,841 --> 01:17:30,900
-You must know.
-You`re married.

1058
01:17:31,110 --> 01:17:32,407
Yes, l`m married.

1059
01:17:32,611 --> 01:17:35,944
But, you know, that`s
not gonna last. l mean....

1060
01:17:36,148 --> 01:17:37,513
Well, you know...

1061
01:17:37,716 --> 01:17:39,911
...l`m not ready.

1062
01:17:41,654 --> 01:17:44,487
ls there something you`re
not telling me?

1063
01:17:44,690 --> 01:17:45,679
No.

1064
01:17:45,891 --> 01:17:48,951
ls there someone else?
Don`t say it`s Lester.

1065
01:17:49,161 --> 01:17:51,356
lt`s me. lt`s just me.

1066
01:17:51,564 --> 01:17:55,523
l guess l haven`t gotten over
my divorce yet, you know?

1067
01:17:55,734 --> 01:17:59,329
And also, l feel unsettled
about my career.

1068
01:17:59,538 --> 01:18:01,563
l`m very ambitious.

1069
01:18:01,774 --> 01:18:05,505
And that`s an area that
l`d like to get consolidated.

1070
01:18:05,711 --> 01:18:08,475
l just feel, you know, unsettled.

1071
01:18:22,795 --> 01:18:24,160
Don`t confuse me.

1072
01:18:24,363 --> 01:18:28,629
-l`m not trying to confuse you.
-l don`t know what l`m doing.

1073
01:18:29,034 --> 01:18:32,197
l better go. l should just leave.

1074
01:18:32,404 --> 01:18:35,168
-You just got here.
-l know, but l--

1075
01:18:35,541 --> 01:18:39,944
-l`m sorry, l didn`t mean--
-No, that`s okay. l`ll see you soon.

1076
01:18:40,145 --> 01:18:42,477
l`ll just-- l`ll be seeing you.

1077
01:18:46,318 --> 01:18:47,785
Please come in.

1078
01:18:49,455 --> 01:18:51,582
We read about it in the paper.

1079
01:18:51,790 --> 01:18:56,193
lt`s a terrible thing.
She`d been coming here for years.

1080
01:18:56,395 --> 01:18:58,363
-Please, sit down.
-Thank you.

1081
01:18:59,164 --> 01:19:03,498
Just a few questions, doctor.
Records show she phoned you here...

1082
01:19:03,702 --> 01:19:06,569
...and at your home a number of times.

1083
01:19:06,772 --> 01:19:10,572
-She worried about her eyes.
-What was she suffering from?

1084
01:19:10,776 --> 01:19:15,804
Nothing serious. She had
light flashes, and they alarmed her.

1085
01:19:16,015 --> 01:19:18,449
l never found anything very wrong.

1086
01:19:18,651 --> 01:19:21,620
l told her it was just
a common occurrence.

1087
01:19:21,820 --> 01:19:25,620
-She was a hypochondriac?
-No. l wouldn`t say that.

1088
01:19:25,824 --> 01:19:27,485
But she was concerned.

1089
01:19:28,160 --> 01:19:31,823
There`s nothing she said
you think might be relevant?

1090
01:19:32,031 --> 01:19:33,828
Personal life? Friends?

1091
01:19:34,033 --> 01:19:36,001
No, not really.

1092
01:19:36,869 --> 01:19:38,769
How did she come to you?

1093
01:19:40,339 --> 01:19:44,002
l honestly can`t remember.
Possibly another patient.

1094
01:19:44,209 --> 01:19:45,642
Can l get that name?

1095
01:19:45,844 --> 01:19:49,302
lt was a while ago,
and l treat so many patients.

1096
01:19:49,515 --> 01:19:52,348
-Might it be in your records?
-No.

1097
01:19:52,551 --> 01:19:55,543
No. l doubt it very much.

1098
01:19:56,455 --> 01:19:59,185
-Sorry to take up your time.
-That`s okay.

1099
01:19:59,391 --> 01:20:02,292
lf you remember anything
that might help...

1100
01:20:02,494 --> 01:20:04,325
-...will you call me?
-Sure.

1101
01:20:04,530 --> 01:20:06,464
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

1102
01:20:16,508 --> 01:20:18,305
You`re having a breakdown!

1103
01:20:18,510 --> 01:20:22,071
They know she phoned me.
l lied. They saw through it.

1104
01:20:22,281 --> 01:20:25,682
-l can`t take this.
-Pull yourself together.

1105
01:20:25,884 --> 01:20:29,012
l did it. lt`s irrevocable,
and l`m gonna pay.

1106
01:20:29,221 --> 01:20:32,987
l had to fight an urge
to come clean to the police.

1107
01:20:33,192 --> 01:20:37,686
l`m in this with you. l helped you.
l don`t wanna go to jail.

1108
01:20:37,896 --> 01:20:42,629
You get ideas about confessing,
and you`ll drag me down with you.

1109
01:20:42,835 --> 01:20:44,803
But l won`t let that happen.

1110
01:20:45,004 --> 01:20:48,371
-ls that a threat?
-Be a man. You`re in the clear.

1111
01:20:48,574 --> 01:20:50,735
-You`ll have me killed?
-Nonsense.

1112
01:20:50,943 --> 01:20:53,776
What did you mean by that remark?

1113
01:20:53,979 --> 01:20:56,573
You`ve helped me in the past. Fine.

1114
01:20:56,782 --> 01:20:58,807
l did you a favor. All right?

1115
01:20:59,018 --> 01:21:03,318
The time to confess was to Miriam
about your mistress.

1116
01:21:03,522 --> 01:21:05,854
Not about this! This is murder.

1117
01:21:06,058 --> 01:21:10,392
You paid for it, l engineered it.
lt`s over! Forget about it!

1118
01:21:10,896 --> 01:21:14,457
-One sin leads to a deeper sin.
-You sound like Papa.

1119
01:21:14,667 --> 01:21:18,068
Adultery, fornication, lies, killing.

1120
01:21:18,270 --> 01:21:21,364
-Can you shut up?
-Or what? You`ll shut me up?

1121
01:21:21,573 --> 01:21:24,633
One phone call,
like pushing a button right?

1122
01:22:01,191 --> 01:22:04,752
l don`t know what`s wrong
with you these days.

1123
01:22:05,862 --> 01:22:08,023
l believe in God, Miriam.

1124
01:22:08,898 --> 01:22:13,733
l know it. Because without God,
the world is a cesspool.

1125
01:22:13,937 --> 01:22:17,100
You drink every day.
You never used to.

1126
01:22:17,307 --> 01:22:18,865
lt`s something new.

1127
01:22:19,075 --> 01:22:21,543
-God, it`s hot.
-Maybe we should go--

1128
01:22:21,745 --> 01:22:25,579
-Don`t tell me what to do, damn it!
-Will you calm down?

1129
01:22:28,451 --> 01:22:31,352
l don`t feel well.
l`m gonna get some air.

1130
01:22:31,554 --> 01:22:33,283
No, you stay here.

1131
01:22:56,780 --> 01:23:00,272
This homeless story is too long,
I want five pages,

1132
01:23:00,483 --> 01:23:02,212
Five real pages,

1133
01:23:02,419 --> 01:23:06,446
His secretary types it tighter,
He doesn`t take a thing out,

1134
01:23:06,656 --> 01:23:08,556
I want Johanson off the show,

1135
01:23:08,758 --> 01:23:12,854
He has cancer, Send him flowers,
He`s not funny,

1136
01:23:13,063 --> 01:23:14,257
I want him off,

1137
01:23:14,464 --> 01:23:19,527
Can`t anyone write funny anymore? I`m
supposed to write everything myself?

1138
01:23:19,736 --> 01:23:22,227
Write, direct and produce it myself?

1139
01:23:22,439 --> 01:23:26,671
I can`t believe this!
Look at the people out there!

1140
01:23:26,876 --> 01:23:31,540
These people are looking for
something funny in their lives!

1141
01:23:31,748 --> 01:23:34,740
They`re waiting for something funny!

1142
01:23:53,303 --> 01:23:55,134
This is terrible.

1143
01:23:55,405 --> 01:23:57,305
What are you doing to me?

1144
01:23:57,507 --> 01:24:00,408
This isn`t a profile
of a creative mind!

1145
01:24:00,810 --> 01:24:05,804
It`s tough for a woman in this
profession, Men always hit on them,

1146
01:24:06,015 --> 01:24:08,984
What is this? When did you shoot that?

1147
01:24:09,185 --> 01:24:12,643
l was lurking around the corner.
l couldn`t resist.

1148
01:24:12,856 --> 01:24:15,324
I don`t wanna do it
in a vulgar way,,,

1149
01:24:15,525 --> 01:24:18,289
,,,and take it off
from what I see here,

1150
01:24:18,495 --> 01:24:21,055
I wanna find out what`s in here,

1151
01:24:21,264 --> 01:24:24,927
So I gotta spend some time,
have dinner together,

1152
01:24:25,135 --> 01:24:27,228
l`m taking over this film.

1153
01:24:27,437 --> 01:24:31,168
-You can`t finish my film.
-l can`t? Read your contract.

1154
01:24:31,374 --> 01:24:34,969
-You promised.
-The idea was to show the real me.

1155
01:24:35,178 --> 01:24:38,705
l`m not perfect, but l don`t
promote values that--

1156
01:24:38,915 --> 01:24:40,280
Let me quote you:

1157
01:24:40,483 --> 01:24:43,281
``--deaden the sensibilities
of democracy.``

1158
01:24:43,486 --> 01:24:46,011
You`re fired. Get out of here!

1159
01:24:46,222 --> 01:24:48,554
Go! Thank you! Goodbye!

1160
01:24:48,892 --> 01:24:53,090
If it bends, it`s funny,
If it breaks, it isn`t,

1161
01:24:54,030 --> 01:24:57,591
Don`t get discouraged.
You have your own vision.

1162
01:24:57,801 --> 01:25:02,170
Why was he so mad? As if nobody
was ever compared to Mussolini.

1163
01:25:02,372 --> 01:25:07,503
l`d no idea you`d cut it like this. l
could`ve told you they`d never use it.

1164
01:25:07,710 --> 01:25:10,042
They want an upbeat profile.

1165
01:25:10,246 --> 01:25:13,807
He`s gonna re-cut it
and make himself into a saint.

1166
01:25:14,017 --> 01:25:18,454
Wendy`s right. l`m jealous of him
with his limos and his money.

1167
01:25:18,655 --> 01:25:22,421
-You have your own style.
-Listen. Marry me. l`m serious.

1168
01:25:22,625 --> 01:25:24,820
That`s all l want. Marry me.

1169
01:25:25,028 --> 01:25:28,259
l`m crazy about you.
My marriage won`t last.

1170
01:25:28,465 --> 01:25:32,265
l gotta talk to you.
Can we sit down for a second?

1171
01:25:32,469 --> 01:25:35,700
l`m not joking.
l`m really nuts about you.

1172
01:25:35,905 --> 01:25:37,805
l`m going away.

1173
01:25:40,043 --> 01:25:42,341
Yeah? Meaning what?

1174
01:25:43,146 --> 01:25:47,674
l`ve got a chance to produce
a couple of shows in London...

1175
01:25:47,884 --> 01:25:50,478
...and, you know, l couldn`t say no.

1176
01:25:51,754 --> 01:25:56,384
-How long are you going for?
-Well, probably three or four months.

1177
01:25:56,926 --> 01:25:59,588
Three or four months?

1178
01:26:00,763 --> 01:26:04,927
Jesus. You`re kidding.
What a discouraging thought.

1179
01:26:05,134 --> 01:26:07,227
But l think it`s a good thing...

1180
01:26:07,437 --> 01:26:11,874
...because l need-- Well,
it will give me a little distance.

1181
01:26:12,075 --> 01:26:15,909
About 3000 miles, to be exact.
When are you leaving?

1182
01:26:16,112 --> 01:26:18,876
Oh, l guess 1 0 days or so.

1183
01:26:20,183 --> 01:26:21,650
God, l`m--

1184
01:26:26,656 --> 01:26:30,490
God, l`m gonna miss you.
l don`t know what to say.

1185
01:26:31,528 --> 01:26:34,827
l`m not gonna see you
for three or four months?

1186
01:26:35,932 --> 01:26:40,460
l feel like l`ve, you know,
been handed a prison sentence.

1187
01:27:09,766 --> 01:27:13,224
Ben, your daughter
will make a beautiful bride.

1188
01:27:14,103 --> 01:27:17,630
This is Barbara,
the sister of my brother-in-law.

1189
01:27:18,241 --> 01:27:23,304
Congratulations. l wish
your daughter all the happiness.

1190
01:27:24,547 --> 01:27:25,536
Thank you.

1191
01:27:27,617 --> 01:27:32,247
Jesus, l`m so self-conscious.
Every single thing on me is rented:

1192
01:27:32,455 --> 01:27:35,515
A rented tux, rented shoes,
rented underwear.

1193
01:27:35,725 --> 01:27:37,955
You look fine. Do me a favor.

1194
01:27:38,161 --> 01:27:42,325
This is your last occasion
with my family. Let`s get along.

1195
01:27:42,532 --> 01:27:44,966
Oh, and this is Dr. Rosenthal.

1196
01:27:45,168 --> 01:27:47,227
-l`m Miriam.
-This is Miriam.

1197
01:27:47,437 --> 01:27:49,405
This is Marian and Peter.

1198
01:27:49,606 --> 01:27:52,131
How do you do? lt`s a pleasure.

1199
01:27:52,342 --> 01:27:54,367
-Judah?
-Yes, Ben?

1200
01:27:54,577 --> 01:27:57,740
l`m so glad you could make it.
lt means a lot.

1201
01:28:00,464 --> 01:28:03,956
What is the matter with you?
You seem so depressed.

1202
01:28:04,168 --> 01:28:07,604
Wendy and l finally
decided to call it quits.

1203
01:28:07,805 --> 01:28:12,640
Even though the last few years
have been terrible, it makes me sad.

1204
01:28:12,843 --> 01:28:15,368
-l`ll have a vodka and tonic.
-Me too.

1205
01:28:15,579 --> 01:28:18,946
You told me it`s been
platonic for a year.

1206
01:28:19,150 --> 01:28:21,448
Once the sex goes, it all goes.

1207
01:28:21,652 --> 01:28:26,715
Last time l was inside a woman was
when l visited the Statue of Liberty.

1208
01:28:35,366 --> 01:28:38,893
Your father`s celebrating
enough for two people.

1209
01:28:39,103 --> 01:28:42,869
He and Ben will get high
and argue about belief in God.

1210
01:28:43,073 --> 01:28:45,337
My dad takes after his Aunt May.

1211
01:28:45,543 --> 01:28:50,503
She rejected the Bible because it had
an unbelievable sense of character.

1212
01:28:51,215 --> 01:28:56,016
l walked in. l said, ``The Waldorf
Astoria.`` You see the centerpieces?

1213
01:28:56,220 --> 01:28:59,212
Did you see the matches?
Lester paid for it.

1214
01:28:59,423 --> 01:29:02,824
l can`t believe a brother
would pay for a wedding.

1215
01:29:03,027 --> 01:29:06,428
That`s the sort of thing
Lester`s always doing.

1216
01:29:06,630 --> 01:29:11,590
-You`ve known him for a long time?
-Since high school.

1217
01:29:24,915 --> 01:29:28,009
They`re pretty.
They`re very, very pretty.

1218
01:29:28,219 --> 01:29:30,187
-Hi, Cliff.
-Cliff, hello.

1219
01:29:30,387 --> 01:29:33,015
Lester, how are you? Good to see you.

1220
01:29:33,224 --> 01:29:36,887
-My fiancée, Halley.
-Congratulations. My wife, Nancy.

1221
01:29:37,862 --> 01:29:40,456
-Jesus, you look wonderful.
-Thank you.

1222
01:29:41,131 --> 01:29:42,598
When did you return?

1223
01:29:43,033 --> 01:29:46,764
l got back this morning.
l`ve been trying to call you.

1224
01:29:46,971 --> 01:29:50,236
l finally won her heart.
What a romantic story.

1225
01:29:50,441 --> 01:29:52,466
We saw each other in London.

1226
01:29:52,676 --> 01:29:55,839
l sent her white roses
around the clock...

1227
01:29:56,046 --> 01:30:00,107
...all the time, for days.
Then l found out she was allergic.

1228
01:30:00,317 --> 01:30:02,444
-Hi.
-Hi. Congratulations.

1229
01:30:02,653 --> 01:30:03,881
Good to see you.

1230
01:30:04,088 --> 01:30:06,454
So l started pleading with her.

1231
01:30:06,657 --> 01:30:09,285
l just begged her day and night.

1232
01:30:09,493 --> 01:30:12,485
And l think it was
the caviar that did it.

1233
01:30:12,696 --> 01:30:15,164
l`ve envied this guy for years.

1234
01:30:15,366 --> 01:30:18,858
He`d show up with a beautiful woman
all the time.

1235
01:30:19,069 --> 01:30:22,038
-But l envy you more now.
-Thank you.

1236
01:30:48,365 --> 01:30:51,027
Standing here
in the presence of God...

1237
01:30:51,235 --> 01:30:55,569
...the guardian of our homes,
ready to enter the bonds of wedlock...

1238
01:30:55,773 --> 01:30:59,265
...answer each of you,
in reverence for God...

1239
01:30:59,476 --> 01:31:02,673
...and in hearing of
the assembly gathered here...

1240
01:31:02,880 --> 01:31:05,314
...so joyously with you.

1241
01:31:13,757 --> 01:31:15,850
-l know the perfect guy.
-Who?

1242
01:31:16,060 --> 01:31:20,019
-He`s brilliant, attractive.
-There`s a hitch. l`m waiting.

1243
01:31:20,230 --> 01:31:24,223
There is, but it sounds worse
than it is. He`s in prison.

1244
01:31:24,435 --> 01:31:28,132
-That`s a drawback.
-Nothing terrible. lnsider trading.

1245
01:31:28,339 --> 01:31:32,002
He made a fortune in the market.
He`ll be out soon.

1246
01:31:32,209 --> 01:31:34,404
Very soon. A couple of years.

1247
01:31:34,611 --> 01:31:36,738
You mean with good behavior.

1248
01:31:55,532 --> 01:31:57,796
l wanted to talk to you.

1249
01:32:03,140 --> 01:32:08,442
What is there really to say?
You know, l`m just stunned still.

1250
01:32:11,181 --> 01:32:14,548
He`s not what you think.
He`s wonderful.

1251
01:32:14,752 --> 01:32:18,017
He`s warm and caring...

1252
01:32:18,222 --> 01:32:22,181
-...and romantic.
-He`s a success, that`s what he is.

1253
01:32:22,393 --> 01:32:26,261
-He`s rich and he`s a success.
-Give me a little credit.

1254
01:32:26,463 --> 01:32:29,955
l always did give you
a little credit until today.

1255
01:32:30,167 --> 01:32:35,161
We used to laugh at him. The silly
shows he puts on, the way he talks.

1256
01:32:35,372 --> 01:32:37,306
He`s endearing.

1257
01:32:38,742 --> 01:32:42,041
This is my worst fear realized.

1258
01:32:47,584 --> 01:32:50,246
l wanted to give you this letter back.

1259
01:32:53,757 --> 01:32:56,851
-lt`s my one love letter.
-lt`s beautiful.

1260
01:32:57,061 --> 01:32:59,689
l`m just the wrong person.

1261
01:33:03,400 --> 01:33:05,493
lt`s probably just as well.

1262
01:33:07,471 --> 01:33:10,565
l plagiarized most of it
from James Joyce.

1263
01:33:11,909 --> 01:33:15,401
You probably wondered
about the Dublin references.

1264
01:33:17,281 --> 01:33:20,808
l hope we can always be friends.

1265
01:34:05,013 --> 01:34:08,414
Off by yourself, huh? You`re like me.

1266
01:34:09,584 --> 01:34:12,382
l always get sad at these events.

1267
01:34:12,587 --> 01:34:14,646
You look very deep in thought.

1268
01:34:17,525 --> 01:34:19,959
l was plotting the perfect murder.

1269
01:34:22,464 --> 01:34:23,954
Movie plot?

1270
01:34:24,899 --> 01:34:26,196
Movie?

1271
01:34:27,335 --> 01:34:31,237
That`s what Ben told me.
He says you make films.

1272
01:34:31,439 --> 01:34:35,773
Yeah, but not that kind.
You know, a different kind.

1273
01:34:37,545 --> 01:34:39,945
l have a great murder story.

1274
01:34:41,249 --> 01:34:43,547
-Yes?
-A great plot.

1275
01:34:44,552 --> 01:34:45,883
Yeah.

1276
01:34:47,856 --> 01:34:51,587
Hey, l`ve had too many to drink.
l mean, forgive me.

1277
01:34:51,793 --> 01:34:53,920
l know you want your privacy.

1278
01:34:54,129 --> 01:34:58,463
No, it`s okay.
l`m not doing anything special.

1279
01:34:59,033 --> 01:35:04,369
Except my murder story
has a very strange twist.

1280
01:35:06,174 --> 01:35:07,471
Yeah?

1281
01:35:09,244 --> 01:35:13,408
Let`s say there`s this man
who is very successful.

1282
01:35:13,615 --> 01:35:15,344
He has everything.

1283
01:35:22,891 --> 01:35:25,086
-Let me ask you something.
-What?

1284
01:35:25,293 --> 01:35:27,261
-Am l a phony?
-Are you what?

1285
01:35:27,462 --> 01:35:30,556
-Am l a phony?
-Are you a little high?

1286
01:35:31,199 --> 01:35:32,689
-He hates me.
-Who?

1287
01:35:32,901 --> 01:35:37,065
Your annoying husband.
Every time l`m with him, l get tense.

1288
01:35:37,272 --> 01:35:39,467
-He`s angry.
-At what?

1289
01:35:39,674 --> 01:35:40,800
Are you kidding?

1290
01:35:41,009 --> 01:35:44,410
He`s got these fantasies
about changing the world.

1291
01:35:44,612 --> 01:35:47,240
ln the end, his films come to nothing.

1292
01:35:47,448 --> 01:35:51,578
He`s gotta grow up.
This is the real world, the big time.

1293
01:35:51,786 --> 01:35:55,620
They don`t pay for high aspirations.
You gotta deliver.

1294
01:35:55,824 --> 01:35:59,419
Not to mention the fact that--
You`re still young.

1295
01:35:59,627 --> 01:36:03,859
-You`re not getting what you deserve.
-Lester, l met somebody.

1296
01:36:07,068 --> 01:36:09,229
That is music to my ears.

1297
01:36:11,005 --> 01:36:13,496
And after the awful deed is done...

1298
01:36:13,708 --> 01:36:17,144
...he finds that he`s plagued
by deep-rooted guilt.

1299
01:36:17,345 --> 01:36:20,803
Little sparks of
his religious background...

1300
01:36:21,015 --> 01:36:25,076
...which he`d rejected,
are suddenly stirred up.

1301
01:36:26,521 --> 01:36:29,513
He hears his father`s voice.

1302
01:36:29,858 --> 01:36:33,726
He imagines that God
is watching his every move.

1303
01:36:33,928 --> 01:36:36,795
Suddenly, it`s not
an empty universe...

1304
01:36:36,998 --> 01:36:39,831
...but a just and moral one...

1305
01:36:40,134 --> 01:36:42,159
...and he`s violated it.

1306
01:36:42,837 --> 01:36:45,067
Now he`s panic-stricken.

1307
01:36:45,340 --> 01:36:48,036
He`s on the verge
of a mental collapse.

1308
01:36:48,243 --> 01:36:52,703
An inch away from confessing
the whole thing to the police.

1309
01:36:53,748 --> 01:36:56,808
And then one morning...

1310
01:36:57,018 --> 01:36:58,849
...he awakens...

1311
01:36:59,454 --> 01:37:03,185
...and the sun is shining,
and his family is around him.

1312
01:37:03,391 --> 01:37:07,555
Mysteriously, the crisis is lifted.

1313
01:37:09,197 --> 01:37:13,497
He takes his family to Europe
and as the months pass...

1314
01:37:13,701 --> 01:37:15,669
...he finds he`s not punished.

1315
01:37:16,070 --> 01:37:18,061
ln fact, he prospers.

1316
01:37:18,673 --> 01:37:21,369
The killing`s attributed
to a drifter...

1317
01:37:21,576 --> 01:37:24,067
...who has many murders to his credit.

1318
01:37:24,279 --> 01:37:27,043
What the hell,
one more doesn`t matter.

1319
01:37:27,715 --> 01:37:29,808
Now he`s scot-free.

1320
01:37:30,351 --> 01:37:33,684
His life is completely
back to normal...

1321
01:37:34,222 --> 01:37:38,921
...back to his protected world
of wealth and privilege.

1322
01:37:39,294 --> 01:37:42,855
Yes, but can he ever really go back?

1323
01:37:44,732 --> 01:37:48,668
Well, people carry sins
around with them, l mean....

1324
01:37:48,870 --> 01:37:53,603
Oh, maybe once in a while
he has a bad moment, but it passes.

1325
01:37:54,008 --> 01:37:56,875
And with time, it all fades.

1326
01:37:57,345 --> 01:37:59,677
Yeah, but-- So then, you know--

1327
01:37:59,881 --> 01:38:03,612
Then his worst beliefs are realized.

1328
01:38:03,818 --> 01:38:06,787
l said it was
a chilling story, didn`t l?

1329
01:38:08,856 --> 01:38:12,485
l think it`d be tough for
somebody to live with that.

1330
01:38:12,694 --> 01:38:16,926
Very few guys could actually live
with something like that.

1331
01:38:17,131 --> 01:38:21,067
People carry awful deeds with them.
What should he do?

1332
01:38:21,269 --> 01:38:22,827
Turn himself in?

1333
01:38:23,404 --> 01:38:25,235
l mean, this is reality.

1334
01:38:25,440 --> 01:38:27,533
ln reality, we rationalize.

1335
01:38:27,742 --> 01:38:31,109
We deny, or we couldn`t go on living.

1336
01:38:34,515 --> 01:38:37,609
l would have him turn himself in...

1337
01:38:37,819 --> 01:38:41,414
...because then your story
assumes tragic proportions.

1338
01:38:41,622 --> 01:38:43,920
Because in the absence of a God...

1339
01:38:44,125 --> 01:38:47,288
...he is forced to assume
that responsibility.

1340
01:38:47,495 --> 01:38:49,827
Then you have tragedy.

1341
01:38:50,164 --> 01:38:53,190
But that`s fiction,
that`s movies. l mean--

1342
01:38:53,401 --> 01:38:57,497
You see too many movies.
l`m talking about reality.

1343
01:38:57,705 --> 01:39:01,732
lf you want a happy ending,
go see a Hollywood movie.

1344
01:39:03,344 --> 01:39:07,371
Come on, darling.
Let`s think about going home, huh?

1345
01:39:07,582 --> 01:39:09,777
Nice talking to you. Good luck.

1346
01:39:09,984 --> 01:39:14,318
We`ll have a wedding like this
for Sharon, and l can`t wait.

1347
01:39:14,522 --> 01:39:16,752
She`ll be radiant.

1348
01:39:17,091 --> 01:39:21,687
-You`re looking very handsome tonight.
-And you look beautiful.

1349
01:39:45,153 --> 01:39:48,384
We are all faced
throughout our lives,,,

1350
01:39:48,589 --> 01:39:51,023
,,,with agonizing decisions,,,

1351
01:39:51,225 --> 01:39:53,216
,,,moral choices,

1352
01:39:53,428 --> 01:39:56,329
Some are on a grand scale,

1353
01:39:56,531 --> 01:40:00,763
Most of these choices
are on lesser points,

1354
